WEBVTT

00:04.754 --> 00:12.887
♪

00:12.887 --> 00:14.764
[ Cellphone ringing ]

00:20.061 --> 00:21.521
I told you
to stop calling me.

00:21.521 --> 00:23.231
I know what
you're about to do.

00:23.231 --> 00:25.483
You're headed
to the D.A.'s office, right?

00:25.483 --> 00:27.944
Turn around.
You're making a mistake.

00:27.944 --> 00:30.363
No, I'm doing what's right.

00:30.363 --> 00:33.241
I'll be fine.
I've secured another position.

00:33.241 --> 00:34.409
The one at DuPont?

00:34.409 --> 00:36.327
Two short phone calls,
three max--

00:36.327 --> 00:37.787
I can make that offer
go away.

00:37.787 --> 00:41.207
Do what you want.
Nothing will change my mind.

00:41.207 --> 00:42.792
Let's play this out.

00:42.792 --> 00:46.171
You take whatever it is
you think you have to the D.A.

00:46.171 --> 00:48.715
And then I call Ron,
who's a personal friend,

00:48.715 --> 00:51.718
<i>and tell him this case
is not worth his time.</i>

00:51.718 --> 00:54.888
<i>Who do you think he listens to
in this scenario?</i>

00:54.888 --> 00:58.016
Me. Because I did him a favor
a while back.

00:58.016 --> 00:59.934
A favor that saved
his marriage.

00:59.934 --> 01:03.938
You wouldn't be on the phone
right now if it were that easy.

01:03.938 --> 01:08.234
How is your dear little Maggie,
by the way?

01:08.234 --> 01:09.652
<i>Peanut allergy, right?</i>

01:09.652 --> 01:11.821
<i>Gosh, those things
are so tough.</i>

01:11.821 --> 01:14.574
<i>Mistakes must happen
all the time.</i>

01:14.574 --> 01:17.744
<i>I heard she went
into anaphylaxis in 2019.</i>

01:17.744 --> 01:20.246
That must have been terrifying.

01:20.246 --> 01:22.207
I guess you just have to hope
her little body

01:22.207 --> 01:25.919
would survive
something like that again.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.921
You're a sick, sick woman.

01:27.921 --> 01:29.589
<i>Put your family first.</i>

01:29.589 --> 01:33.426
This crusade is not
your passion-- they are.

01:33.426 --> 01:35.720
You stay away from my family.

01:35.720 --> 01:40.558
♪

01:40.558 --> 01:42.060
[ Horn honking ]

01:42.060 --> 01:43.937
[ Cellphone rings ]

01:43.937 --> 01:45.230
Looks like he's leaving.

01:45.230 --> 01:46.606
<i>I've done
everything I can.</i>

01:46.606 --> 01:48.274
You need to get
those documents.

01:48.274 --> 01:50.694
What exactly are you
asking me to do?

01:50.694 --> 01:53.113
Whatever needs
to be done.

01:53.113 --> 02:13.758
♪

02:13.758 --> 02:16.302
He spotted me.
He's trying to lose me.

02:16.302 --> 02:17.554
<i>Well, go after him.</i>

02:17.554 --> 02:19.222
[ Tires screech, car crashes ]

02:19.222 --> 02:24.269
♪

02:24.269 --> 02:26.229
What's going on?
The dude crashed.

02:26.229 --> 02:28.440
<i>I don't care.
We need those papers.</i>

02:28.440 --> 02:30.025
[ Siren wailing ]
<i>Figure it out.</i>

02:30.025 --> 02:32.610
Negative.
Cops are on site.

02:32.610 --> 02:34.612
I'm not taking
that kind of heat.

02:34.612 --> 02:35.822
<i>This is what
you're hired for.</i>

02:35.822 --> 02:37.407
<i>We need those papers.</i>
I'm sorry.

02:37.407 --> 02:38.992
I'm out of here.

02:38.992 --> 02:50.670
♪

02:50.670 --> 02:53.214
[ Beeping ]

02:55.759 --> 02:58.386
Senator Panabaker,
Director Cooper,

02:58.386 --> 03:00.263
this is
Representative Hudson.

03:00.263 --> 03:01.848
How do you do?

03:01.848 --> 03:03.850
I appreciate you both

03:03.850 --> 03:05.393
being able to meet
on such short notice.

03:05.393 --> 03:08.021
Look, Clayton, I have time
for formalities

03:08.021 --> 03:09.856
like I have time
for long walks on the beach.

03:09.856 --> 03:12.692
You got us here.
What's this about?

03:12.692 --> 03:14.361
Well, Arthur and I
have some questions

03:14.361 --> 03:16.196
about your FBI task force,

03:16.196 --> 03:18.198
and no one seems
to be able to answer.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.867
I mean, we had a heck of a time
even getting your name,

03:20.867 --> 03:22.786
Director Cooper.
That's intentional.

03:22.786 --> 03:25.580
The nature of our work
is highly classified.

03:25.580 --> 03:27.499
Oh, I understand that, really.

03:27.499 --> 03:29.501
And from what little information
I've been able to glean,

03:29.501 --> 03:31.503
it seems that
you've helped close

03:31.503 --> 03:33.380
some of Main Justice's
biggest cases.

03:33.380 --> 03:34.964
That's impressive.

03:34.964 --> 03:38.510
However, it doesn't explain
your exorbitant budget.

03:38.510 --> 03:43.848
$282.7 million last year alone,
to be exact.

03:43.848 --> 03:47.268
That's still less than 3%
of the FBI's overall budget.

03:47.268 --> 03:48.561
[ Chuckles ]

03:48.561 --> 03:51.356
It's an awful lot
for a single task force.

03:51.356 --> 03:54.359
How is your budget
being allocated,

03:54.359 --> 03:57.362
and what is it exactly
that you do?

03:58.988 --> 04:01.074
We work with gathered
intelligence to detain

04:01.074 --> 04:03.702
and apprehend criminal suspects
around the world--

04:03.702 --> 04:06.162
criminals that
wouldn't otherwise be

04:06.162 --> 04:07.372
on the FBI's radar.

04:07.372 --> 04:09.290
We've thwarted
terrorist attacks,

04:09.290 --> 04:10.583
stopped assassinations,

04:10.583 --> 04:12.293
disbanded
global conspiracies,

04:12.293 --> 04:14.462
exposed
human-trafficking rings

04:14.462 --> 04:15.797
domestically and overseas.

04:15.797 --> 04:18.758
Specifics.
We want specifics.

04:18.758 --> 04:21.386
You must have internal case
files that break it all down.

04:21.386 --> 04:22.762
Of course.

04:22.762 --> 04:24.723
I'm just not at liberty
to divulge those.

04:24.723 --> 04:25.890
Says who?

04:25.890 --> 04:27.517
Alright, Congress
and the American people

04:27.517 --> 04:29.060
deserve to know where
their tax dollars are going.

04:29.060 --> 04:31.062
Give me a break, Clayton.

04:31.062 --> 04:33.106
It's a nice sales pitch,

04:33.106 --> 04:35.275
but we both know
too much government oversight

04:35.275 --> 04:38.528
can be harmful to the FBI's
ability to work covertly.

04:38.528 --> 04:40.613
You don't just get to operate
in the blind, Cynthia.

04:40.613 --> 04:42.198
Harold's task force

04:42.198 --> 04:44.117
does incredibly
important work.

04:44.117 --> 04:46.077
The funding
is being well spent.

04:46.077 --> 04:47.495
You have my word.

04:49.080 --> 04:51.708
Well, we'll see how your word
holds up in front of a judge.

04:51.708 --> 04:55.295
Now, unless one of you
is willing to elaborate,

04:55.295 --> 04:57.672
I think we're done here.

04:57.672 --> 05:04.512
♪

05:04.512 --> 05:06.848
I appreciate you
defending us in there.

05:06.848 --> 05:10.393
It means a lot,
which makes this harder to say.

05:11.978 --> 05:14.481
Our case files
have been compromised.

05:14.481 --> 05:16.441
What the hell
does that mean?

05:16.441 --> 05:18.401
When Reddington was alone
in the post office

05:18.401 --> 05:20.445
during the Wujing incident,

05:20.445 --> 05:23.615
he gained access
to our computer network

05:23.615 --> 05:25.617
and removed any mention
of himself

05:25.617 --> 05:26.826
from our
permanent records.

05:26.826 --> 05:29.412
He wh-- What?

05:29.412 --> 05:31.164
How could you
keep this from me?

05:31.164 --> 05:32.665
Cynthia, I apologize.

05:32.665 --> 05:34.751
But at the time,
omitting this information

05:34.751 --> 05:36.336
and carrying on
with our casework

05:36.336 --> 05:38.421
seemed like
the right thing...
I defended you.

05:38.421 --> 05:40.256
I always defend you.

05:40.256 --> 05:43.385
If a judge allows them
to subpoena those files

05:43.385 --> 05:44.928
and they've clearly
been tampered with,

05:44.928 --> 05:46.930
both of our careers
will be on the line.

05:46.930 --> 05:48.807
Not to mention the fact
that you've barely

05:48.807 --> 05:51.810
had any convictions this year,
just a bunch of prison breaks

05:51.810 --> 05:53.728
and dead bodies
splayed out on the floor.

05:53.728 --> 05:55.730
That's a bit
of an exaggeration.

05:55.730 --> 05:57.524
Is it?
You fix this.

05:57.524 --> 06:01.069
I don't know how,
but you fix it.

06:05.907 --> 06:07.575
Harold, why so glum?

06:07.575 --> 06:08.993
Oh, I don't know.

06:08.993 --> 06:10.412
Maybe because
I've got a senator

06:10.412 --> 06:12.580
and congressmen
breathing down my neck

06:12.580 --> 06:14.374
trying to get access
to our files.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.209
Files that have been
significantly compromised

06:16.209 --> 06:17.669
because of you.

06:17.669 --> 06:19.879
Well, we've found ourselves
under siege before.

06:19.879 --> 06:23.800
Perhaps it's time yet again
to hunker down,

06:23.800 --> 06:26.845
take a moment,
and let it blow over.

06:26.845 --> 06:28.513
Actually, it's not
going to blow over.

06:28.513 --> 06:30.390
They've secured a hearing
before a judge for today.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.976
Then we let the wheels
of justice

06:32.976 --> 06:35.562
grind at their characteristic
snail's pace

06:35.562 --> 06:36.730
and be fine about it.

06:36.730 --> 06:38.106
Are you hearing anything
I'm saying?

06:38.106 --> 06:40.567
The future of this task force
is on the line.

06:40.567 --> 06:43.403
I need you to start giving us
substantial cases again.

06:43.403 --> 06:44.612
Cases that can demonstrate

06:44.612 --> 06:46.614
to the Justice Department
and Congress

06:46.614 --> 06:48.658
that we get results
and can justify

06:48.658 --> 06:50.493
our significant expenditures.

06:50.493 --> 06:52.579
We've always had
a "we scratch your back,

06:52.579 --> 06:54.080
you scratch ours"
arrangement.

06:54.080 --> 06:56.499
But now I'm not so sure.

06:56.499 --> 06:57.709
Well, perk up.

06:57.709 --> 07:00.086
I have a few new ideas
to discuss

07:00.086 --> 07:02.088
that will scratch
everyone's back.

07:02.088 --> 07:05.925
First, I need you to look
into this container ship.

07:05.925 --> 07:09.512
It's scheduled to arrive
at the port of Baltimore.

07:09.512 --> 07:11.598
This is the hull number.

07:11.598 --> 07:13.308
In the meantime,

07:13.308 --> 07:17.312
I have another case
of the utmost priority.

07:17.312 --> 07:20.065
Blair Foster,
Washington, D.C.'s

07:20.065 --> 07:22.275
most infamous fixer.

07:22.275 --> 07:25.779
If corruption is what Dorf
and Hudson are looking for,

07:25.779 --> 07:29.115
then let's shine a light
under every rock in town

07:29.115 --> 07:32.619
and show them what
real corruption looks like.

07:32.619 --> 07:35.955
Ms. Foster has
a legitimate law practice,

07:35.955 --> 07:38.166
but her real
stock-in-trade

07:38.166 --> 07:41.544
is her off-the-books
private services.

07:41.544 --> 07:43.922
She's stealthy, discreet,

07:43.922 --> 07:46.800
has a way
of burying scandals

07:46.800 --> 07:49.302
before the corpses
are even cold.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.470
I know of Ms. Foster.

07:50.470 --> 07:52.305
Her reputation certainly
proceeds her.

07:52.305 --> 07:53.682
Bureau's been trying to build
a case against her

07:53.682 --> 07:55.642
for years to no avail.

07:55.642 --> 07:57.686
Well, one
of her biggest clients

07:57.686 --> 08:00.230
is corporate giant
Moder & Sons.

08:00.230 --> 08:01.773
There have been whispers
in recent years

08:01.773 --> 08:04.651
of carcinogenic materials

08:04.651 --> 08:06.736
in some of their
consumer products.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.655
And I believe
the only reason

08:08.655 --> 08:12.826
no lawsuit has ever come
to fruition is Foster.

08:12.826 --> 08:17.205
She runs a legitimate boutique
law firm employing lawyers,

08:17.205 --> 08:20.417
legal aides, clerks,
and investigators,

08:20.417 --> 08:22.669
but they rarely file cases--

08:22.669 --> 08:25.880
strange given the power
and influence they wield.

08:25.880 --> 08:29.300
And when they do, the cases
almost always settle or go away.

08:29.300 --> 08:33.179
She employs a disproportionate
number of investigators

08:33.179 --> 08:35.015
for a firm this size.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.267
So it's her work as a fixer
that keeps the lights on?

08:37.267 --> 08:39.060
It appears so.

08:39.060 --> 08:41.938
Most recently, Reddington
believes that Foster

08:41.938 --> 08:43.773
is responsible
for the car accident

08:43.773 --> 08:46.693
of a mid-level employee
at the Moder & Sons corporation.

08:46.693 --> 08:48.862
Why would she care
about mid-level employees?

08:48.862 --> 08:51.531
Reddington suspects it was
her effort to silence him

08:51.531 --> 08:53.825
on some internal matter
at Moder & Sons.

08:53.825 --> 08:56.578
Luckily, the man,
Lawrence Whitaker,

08:56.578 --> 08:57.871
survived the accident.

08:57.871 --> 08:59.873
Siya: This may be
just what we need.

08:59.873 --> 09:02.042
If the scandals Foster buried
are as explosive

09:02.042 --> 09:05.920
as Reddington claims
and we unearth them,

09:05.920 --> 09:09.257
then Hudson and Dorf
and all the rest of D.C.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.217
will have bigger fish
to fry than us.

09:11.217 --> 09:14.471
Ressler, Malik--
visit Whitaker at the hospital.

09:14.471 --> 09:16.348
See what you find.

09:16.348 --> 09:21.770
♪

09:21.770 --> 09:23.063
Siya: We're so sorry

09:23.063 --> 09:25.106
you're going through this,
Mrs. Whitaker.

09:25.106 --> 09:28.735
The impact from the crash
caused a subdural hematoma,

09:28.735 --> 09:32.155
but he should be off
the ventilator soon.

09:32.155 --> 09:34.115
I still can't believe
this happened.

09:34.115 --> 09:36.910
He's usually such
a cautious driver.

09:36.910 --> 09:40.163
He's just been under
so much stress at work.

09:40.163 --> 09:42.665
We have reason to believe
that your husband

09:42.665 --> 09:44.084
may have been in possession

09:44.084 --> 09:47.545
of some damaging material
about Moder & Sons.

09:47.545 --> 09:50.256
Is that true?

09:50.256 --> 09:54.135
He found out something
he wasn't supposed to.

09:54.135 --> 09:56.930
He said that he couldn't talk
about it yet

09:56.930 --> 09:59.557
and that he might not be
working there much longer.

09:59.557 --> 10:01.101
Were they threatening
to fire him?

10:01.101 --> 10:03.436
I think they were trying
to push him out.

10:03.436 --> 10:06.147
He started to get paranoid
leading up to the accident.

10:06.147 --> 10:08.608
He said that people were
following him

10:08.608 --> 10:10.652
outside the house
and work.

10:10.652 --> 10:12.612
I never saw anyone.

10:12.612 --> 10:14.781
But he swears he did.

10:14.781 --> 10:15.824
I wish I knew more.

10:15.824 --> 10:17.283
We'll look into it.

10:17.283 --> 10:19.744
See if we can find out
if he was being followed.

10:19.744 --> 10:23.498
In the meantime, we'll station
an officer outside the door.

10:23.498 --> 10:25.375
Just call us when he wakes up.

10:25.375 --> 10:29.546
♪

10:29.546 --> 10:31.006
Hi, it's Emily Larson.

10:31.006 --> 10:32.799
The FBI is here questioning
Mr. Whitaker's wife.

10:32.799 --> 10:35.135
[ Sighs ]
Of course they are.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.928
What about Whitaker's
personal effects?

10:36.928 --> 10:38.888
Did you find the documents
I'd asked you about?

10:38.888 --> 10:40.140
They'd be
in a messenger bag.

10:40.140 --> 10:41.766
I went through everything.
I'm sorry.

10:41.766 --> 10:44.811
There's nothing here.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.730
Where the hell is it?

11:00.076 --> 11:01.036
Siya: Larry Whitaker's wife
told us

11:02.245 --> 11:03.913
he believed he was being
followed leading up

11:03.913 --> 11:05.040
to the day
of the accident.

11:05.040 --> 11:06.207
I pulled
the security footage

11:06.207 --> 11:09.085
from buildings
nearby Moder & Sons.

11:09.085 --> 11:11.212
Over the past week,
including the day of the crash,

11:11.212 --> 11:13.298
the same vehicle
with the same driver

11:13.298 --> 11:14.758
was stationed outside.

11:14.758 --> 11:16.426
Were you able
to run the plates?

11:16.426 --> 11:17.552
The District of Columbia

11:17.552 --> 11:19.304
doesn't have registration
for the vehicle.

11:19.304 --> 11:21.139
We've had no luck
with facial recognition.

11:21.139 --> 11:23.099
I've run it through
all our databases,

11:23.099 --> 11:24.351
and it's like he's a ghost.

11:24.351 --> 11:27.145
If he's done
the fixer's dirty work,

11:27.145 --> 11:30.231
someone in criminal world
should be able to I.D. him.

11:30.231 --> 11:32.609
I think we should get this
over to Raymond.

11:32.609 --> 11:34.944
I agree.
He's still in town.

11:34.944 --> 11:36.654
Take it to him
over at the warehouse.

11:36.654 --> 11:38.490
See if he can help.

11:41.076 --> 11:43.119
I couldn't place it.

11:43.119 --> 11:46.331
But I swear I recognize him
from somewhere.

11:46.331 --> 11:50.794
Maybe Panama when we were
doing contracting for Hector?

11:50.794 --> 11:51.795
Could be.

11:51.795 --> 11:54.130
Certainly looks familiar.

11:54.130 --> 11:57.384
You don't have a name?
Not even an alias?

11:57.384 --> 11:58.843
No.

11:58.843 --> 12:00.720
But after viewing
the footage,

12:00.720 --> 12:02.305
I'm convinced
he's military.

12:02.305 --> 12:05.100
His protocols
and procedures,

12:05.100 --> 12:07.310
the way he surveils...

12:07.310 --> 12:09.521
[ Laughs ]

12:09.521 --> 12:10.730
Don't laugh.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.148
Wait till you're my age.

12:12.148 --> 12:14.484
First the knees,
then the eyes.

12:14.484 --> 12:16.611
Tell that
to my right shoulder.

12:18.405 --> 12:21.032
Did you see the tattoo
on his finger?

12:21.032 --> 12:23.827
Those numbers
can mean anything.

12:23.827 --> 12:26.246
Or something.

12:26.246 --> 12:29.791
The Black Wasps
are identified as 4895.

12:29.791 --> 12:32.252
He could be
Cuban special forces.

12:32.252 --> 12:35.171
You should reach out
to Manny. Manny.

12:35.171 --> 12:37.841
Ah, Dembe, we should
hang out more.

12:37.841 --> 12:39.175
I miss us.

12:39.175 --> 12:42.012
Remember that night
in Saint-Tropez

12:42.012 --> 12:43.847
with Thomas and Yvette?

12:43.847 --> 12:45.515
What a gas.

12:45.515 --> 12:48.435
Oh, my gosh, Yvette.

12:48.435 --> 12:49.686
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

12:49.686 --> 12:51.980
I tried to forget.

12:51.980 --> 12:55.525
Excuse me.
You're on speaker.

12:55.525 --> 12:58.153
Ressler: <i>Whitaker just woke up.
We're heading out.</i>

12:58.153 --> 12:59.779
<i>Any luck on the I.D.?</i>
We're working on it.

12:59.779 --> 13:02.782
I'll report back soon.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.200
I better get going.

13:04.200 --> 13:07.495
I guess
I better get going, too.

13:07.495 --> 13:09.497
Get going where?

13:09.497 --> 13:10.832
Havana.

13:10.832 --> 13:12.959
Raymond, just call Manny.

13:12.959 --> 13:16.212
These things are always
better handled in person.

13:17.505 --> 13:21.926
I had requested some research
files from a few years back

13:21.926 --> 13:23.845
of some of our products.

13:23.845 --> 13:26.014
I'm in quality control,

13:26.014 --> 13:30.352
and I stumbled quite
accidentally upon a study

13:30.352 --> 13:33.772
that stated
that Spring 'N Shine

13:33.772 --> 13:37.859
unequivocally contained
carcinogenic compounds.

13:37.859 --> 13:39.235
What's
"Spring 'N Shine"?

13:39.235 --> 13:41.154
It's the number-one
multi-purpose cleaner

13:41.154 --> 13:45.241
on the market
for 11 years running.

13:45.241 --> 13:48.203
Which is why I was surprised
to find the study.

13:48.203 --> 13:51.623
But Moder & Sons
buried the report.

13:51.623 --> 13:55.752
They didn't even try to recall
the toxic product.

13:55.752 --> 13:58.171
Bottles of it had been
in circulation for years

13:58.171 --> 14:01.132
after the study was completed.

14:01.132 --> 14:03.968
People died...

14:03.968 --> 14:05.470
children.

14:08.306 --> 14:11.101
I couldn't in good conscience
remain silent.

14:11.101 --> 14:12.602
So what did you do?

14:12.602 --> 14:14.646
I told a co-worker who I thought
I could trust,

14:14.646 --> 14:18.858
that I was thinking of going
public with what I found.

14:18.858 --> 14:20.485
And the very next day,

14:20.485 --> 14:23.571
Blair Foster was standing
in my office.

14:23.571 --> 14:25.782
Did she try
to intimidate you?

14:25.782 --> 14:27.867
Not at first.

14:27.867 --> 14:29.911
She was friendly.

14:29.911 --> 14:31.579
We spoke about family.

14:31.579 --> 14:34.457
When she heard that my daughter
was wait-listed at Sidwell,

14:34.457 --> 14:35.959
she said that she could
get her in

14:35.959 --> 14:37.961
with a healthy
financial-aid package.

14:37.961 --> 14:40.088
So she was trying
to bribe you.

14:40.088 --> 14:41.297
Do you have any proof?

14:41.297 --> 14:44.092
She never put anything
in writing.

14:44.092 --> 14:48.096
It was all very... casual.

14:48.096 --> 14:51.641
And when I didn't take the bait,
she started to threaten me--

14:51.641 --> 14:53.768
subtly...

14:53.768 --> 14:56.396
then not so subtle.

14:56.396 --> 14:58.148
And she thought
that the evidence

14:58.148 --> 15:00.316
of the study was destroyed.

15:00.316 --> 15:03.069
But I downloaded
and printed out a copy

15:03.069 --> 15:05.155
before they wiped the server.

15:05.155 --> 15:08.324
Do you have a copy
of that report on you?

15:08.324 --> 15:10.410
No, it's in my car.

15:10.410 --> 15:12.537
Oh, man.

15:15.206 --> 15:16.583
Little help, please.

15:16.583 --> 15:17.709
One minute.

15:17.709 --> 15:22.839
♪

15:22.839 --> 15:24.007
That was work-related.

15:24.007 --> 15:25.175
How can I help you?

15:25.175 --> 15:27.344
I got in an accident yesterday.

15:27.344 --> 15:29.012
I was told my car
got towed here.

15:29.012 --> 15:30.847
Alright, I just need
your license.

15:30.847 --> 15:33.141
I lost it
in the accident.

15:33.141 --> 15:36.936
I have my registration.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.272
It's my corporate car.

15:39.272 --> 15:40.607
I'm very sorry, sir,

15:40.607 --> 15:42.650
but I do need
a valid license with a photo.

15:42.650 --> 15:46.404
Listen, it's been
a really rough 24 hours.

15:46.404 --> 15:49.240
My laptop and work stuff
are in there.

15:49.240 --> 15:51.034
My car's totaled.

15:51.034 --> 15:53.286
Can't you just help
a guy out?

15:54.329 --> 15:56.081
[ Cellphone dings ]
It's from Herbie.

15:56.081 --> 15:57.916
He spoke to local PD.

15:57.916 --> 15:59.084
Mr. Whitaker's car

15:59.084 --> 16:00.210
is at "M" Street Towing
in Southwest.

16:00.210 --> 16:01.461
He sent me the address.

16:01.461 --> 16:14.724
♪

16:14.724 --> 16:16.935
Ressler: FBI.

16:16.935 --> 16:18.478
Hi.
Can I help you?

16:18.478 --> 16:20.855
Agents Ressler and Malik.
We need to locate a vehicle.

16:20.855 --> 16:24.943
It's a black Mercedes
registered to a Larry Whitaker.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.319
Is he
in some kind of trouble?

16:26.319 --> 16:27.987
He just came by
to grab his things.

16:27.987 --> 16:30.490
He's probably
still here.

16:30.490 --> 16:38.373
♪

16:38.373 --> 16:41.418
Huh.
The guy was just here.

16:42.711 --> 16:45.672
So was his bag.
Now it's gone.

16:51.469 --> 17:06.234
♪

17:06.234 --> 17:09.362
Senator Dorf,
I've received your motion

17:09.362 --> 17:12.866
to compel the Bureau
to comply with your subpoena

17:12.866 --> 17:15.243
seeking documents related
to the budget

17:15.243 --> 17:18.663
and casework
of Task Force 836.

17:18.663 --> 17:23.710
I see that both parties have
submitted extensive documents.

17:23.710 --> 17:26.755
Anything I need to know
before we dive in?

17:26.755 --> 17:28.381
To reiterate,
Judge Hurban,

17:28.381 --> 17:31.051
our refusal to turn
over records to Senator Dorf

17:31.051 --> 17:34.054
isn't an attempt to obfuscate
what our team does

17:34.054 --> 17:36.014
or how
we allocate our funds.

17:36.014 --> 17:37.932
It's an attempt
to protect my agents

17:37.932 --> 17:39.893
and our sources,
plain and simple.

17:39.893 --> 17:41.269
All of their lives
could be in danger

17:41.269 --> 17:43.104
if the nature of our work
was made public.

17:43.104 --> 17:45.065
Panabaker: And as a sitting
member of Congress

17:45.065 --> 17:46.399
who's privy to more details

17:46.399 --> 17:49.944
than most regarding
FBI Task Force number 836,

17:49.944 --> 17:51.363
I wholeheartedly endorse

17:51.363 --> 17:53.990
Assistant Director
Cooper's position.

17:53.990 --> 17:56.785
Senator Dorf,
Representative Hudson.

17:56.785 --> 17:58.828
Any final remarks?

17:58.828 --> 18:01.122
Oversight
on law enforcement

18:01.122 --> 18:03.875
is a necessary check
and balance.

18:03.875 --> 18:05.418
It's our responsibility,

18:05.418 --> 18:07.921
especially in this current
political climate,

18:07.921 --> 18:09.422
when we've seen
what can happen

18:09.422 --> 18:13.009
when law-enforcement
agencies' authority

18:13.009 --> 18:14.344
goes unchecked.

18:14.344 --> 18:16.721
We're simply asking
for transparency.

18:16.721 --> 18:20.934
While I hear you, Senator,
my job is not to be concerned

18:20.934 --> 18:25.063
with the "current political
climate"-- only facts.

18:25.063 --> 18:27.774
I think I have
everything I need.

18:27.774 --> 18:30.694
I will try to be expeditious.

18:30.694 --> 18:38.993
♪

18:38.993 --> 18:40.120
Hola, Manny.

18:40.120 --> 18:43.957
[ Chuckles ] Red!

18:43.957 --> 18:46.418
<i>Como estas,</i>
my brother?

18:46.418 --> 18:49.004
Well.

18:49.004 --> 18:50.463
You seem very well.

18:50.463 --> 18:53.425
I guess I've got some
catching up to do.

18:55.093 --> 18:57.012
So what brings you here?

18:57.012 --> 18:58.680
I have something

18:58.680 --> 19:00.473
I really want
to show you.

19:00.473 --> 19:07.605
♪

19:07.605 --> 19:09.024
You flew
all the way to Cuba

19:09.024 --> 19:10.316
to show me
some old boxing gloves?

19:10.316 --> 19:13.695
Yeah, well...
they are old, in fact,

19:13.695 --> 19:16.156
almost 50 years old.

19:16.156 --> 19:20.368
They haven't been used
since the '76 Games.

19:23.413 --> 19:26.249
Those aren't...
They can't be...

19:26.249 --> 19:29.169
I know they are,
and they can.

19:29.169 --> 19:32.005
Teofilo Stevenson's gloves
from one

19:32.005 --> 19:35.425
of his iconic
Olympic performances.

19:35.425 --> 19:39.095
I remember years ago,
you told me

19:39.095 --> 19:42.265
how your father would pile
you and your brothers

19:42.265 --> 19:45.060
in the back
of his Chevy Bel Air

19:45.060 --> 19:48.355
and take you over
to the Esquela de Boxeo

19:48.355 --> 19:51.524
to watch Stevenson train.

19:51.524 --> 19:54.861
You told me you'd sit there
for hours on end,

19:54.861 --> 19:57.989
just totally mesmerized.

19:57.989 --> 19:59.866
He was something
to behold.

19:59.866 --> 20:03.787
So skilled with his feet,
especially for a heavyweight.

20:03.787 --> 20:07.248
A hero among men.

20:07.248 --> 20:10.585
Man, those are some

20:10.585 --> 20:14.297
of the best memories
of my whole life.

20:14.297 --> 20:17.550
Well, they're all yours...

20:17.550 --> 20:21.388
if you can help me
with this guy.

20:22.889 --> 20:25.517
I need an I.D.
and location.

20:25.517 --> 20:29.020
I suspect he's a former
Black Wasp.

20:29.020 --> 20:30.814
I can't.

20:30.814 --> 20:32.065
Too dangerous.

20:32.065 --> 20:33.233
You mess with guys
like that,

20:33.233 --> 20:35.485
you end up with a bullet
in your head.

20:35.485 --> 20:37.737
Where's your sense
of adventure?

20:37.737 --> 20:41.533
And you can't at least put out
some feelers for me?

20:41.533 --> 20:45.245
The last time I tried
to help you I.D. someone,

20:45.245 --> 20:50.125
you shot two of my police
contacts in front of me.

20:50.125 --> 20:52.544
I should have known
you had an agenda.

20:52.544 --> 20:55.547
It's probably why Weecha
left you for Adolfo.

20:55.547 --> 20:57.841
Left me?!
She didn't leave me.

20:57.841 --> 21:00.927
It's considerably more
complicated than that.

21:00.927 --> 21:02.095
Who told you, anyway?

21:02.095 --> 21:05.181
Straight from
the horse's mouth.

21:05.181 --> 21:07.225
Weecha comes
through here a lot.

21:07.225 --> 21:09.561
Always comes in
for a drink.

21:09.561 --> 21:12.772
She gets mail here.
She calls.

21:12.772 --> 21:14.858
Well, if you change
your mind,

21:14.858 --> 21:18.653
I'll be in town overnight
in that little inn

21:18.653 --> 21:22.449
a block over
from Callejon de Hamel.

21:22.449 --> 21:24.909
[ Inhales sharply ]

21:28.288 --> 21:30.457
As for the gloves,

21:30.457 --> 21:32.959
once they leave Cuba
with me...

21:32.959 --> 21:34.085
[ Zipper closes ]

21:34.085 --> 21:35.503
...they don't come back.

21:35.503 --> 21:41.176
♪

21:41.176 --> 21:44.346
Oh, if you happen to talk
to Weecha, please,

21:44.346 --> 21:46.264
tell her where
she can find me.

21:46.264 --> 21:54.189
♪

21:54.189 --> 21:56.232
Richard, please come in.

21:56.232 --> 21:59.152
We need to talk... now.

21:59.152 --> 22:02.697
Could you give Mr. Moder
and me a moment alone, please?

22:04.491 --> 22:06.993
[ Door opens, closes ]

22:06.993 --> 22:09.621
The FBI is
at our offices

22:09.621 --> 22:12.624
asking questions
with a warrant.

22:12.624 --> 22:14.000
I thought you were
handling this.

22:14.000 --> 22:15.168
I am.

22:15.168 --> 22:16.378
Whitaker somehow got
on their radar,

22:16.378 --> 22:18.380
but we secured the report.

22:18.380 --> 22:20.340
Without it, there's no case.
We're safe.

22:20.340 --> 22:23.134
What about Dr. Feinberg?
He wrote the report.

22:23.134 --> 22:24.552
We have his NDA.
We're covered.

22:24.552 --> 22:26.304
Do you think he's gonna
honor that NDA

22:26.304 --> 22:28.515
now that there's
a federal investigation?

22:28.515 --> 22:31.101
I don't want
any loose ends.

22:31.101 --> 22:33.603
He needs
to be taken care of.

22:35.814 --> 22:38.525
There are smarter ways
out of all of this.

22:38.525 --> 22:40.318
What if I could get
the investigation

22:40.318 --> 22:42.779
to go away altogether?

22:42.779 --> 22:44.322
How on earth
would you do that?

22:44.322 --> 22:45.532
You need to trust me.

22:45.532 --> 22:47.909
I told you this
is gonna be clean,

22:47.909 --> 22:49.869
and it will be.

22:49.869 --> 22:52.872
Just let me do my job.

22:52.872 --> 22:54.207
Pritchard:
I really appreciate

22:54.207 --> 22:55.375
you showing up
for me today.

22:55.375 --> 22:56.918
Of course.
You're doing great.

22:56.918 --> 22:59.212
Alright?
See you next week?
I'll be here.

22:59.212 --> 23:01.256
And if I'm not, dear God,
come find me.

23:01.256 --> 23:08.722
♪

23:08.722 --> 23:10.223
Agent Ressler.

23:10.223 --> 23:11.641
I'm Blair Foster.

23:11.641 --> 23:14.144
But you already know
who I am, don't you?

23:14.144 --> 23:15.395
I know you don't drink,

23:15.395 --> 23:17.397
so why don't I buy you
a cup of coffee?

23:17.397 --> 23:20.233
If you want to talk,
we can do it here.

23:28.950 --> 23:29.909
I just wanted to take
a private moment

23:30.994 --> 23:32.287
to let you know
that Moder & Sons

23:32.287 --> 23:35.040
intends to fully cooperate
with your investigation.

23:35.040 --> 23:38.501
We care deeply about
our employees and consumers.

23:38.501 --> 23:40.795
Well, you don't seem
to care too deeply

23:40.795 --> 23:42.756
about Larry Whitaker.

23:42.756 --> 23:45.050
Larry Whitaker
is a troubled man.

23:45.050 --> 23:47.927
He started spreading damaging
lies about the company

23:47.927 --> 23:50.722
after he'd been passed over
for a promotion.

23:50.722 --> 23:51.931
He was embittered
by a system

23:51.931 --> 23:54.059
where he was
no longer advancing.

23:54.059 --> 23:56.853
I tried to reason with him,
but I can't help someone

23:56.853 --> 23:58.897
who doesn't want
to help himself.

23:58.897 --> 24:01.649
Rich Moder is one
of the most ethical

24:01.649 --> 24:04.652
and thoughtful C.E.O.s
I've ever come across.

24:04.652 --> 24:06.654
And trust me, I've worked
with a lot of them.

24:06.654 --> 24:08.323
If he's so ethical,
then why would he have

24:08.323 --> 24:10.617
knowingly allowed
carcinogenic materials

24:10.617 --> 24:12.077
to stay on store shelves?

24:12.077 --> 24:14.662
That's a fictitious narrative
being driven

24:14.662 --> 24:18.375
by a man
who is unhappy and unhinged.

24:18.375 --> 24:19.876
This isn't gonna
go anywhere.

24:19.876 --> 24:22.337
This is a waste
of your time.

24:22.337 --> 24:25.715
You're meant for something
so much bigger than all this.

24:25.715 --> 24:28.426
I've done my homework
on you. Clearly.

24:28.426 --> 24:30.178
You found me
at my NA meeting.

24:30.178 --> 24:33.181
Son of a cop who was
killed in the line of duty.

24:33.181 --> 24:37.352
The son goes on to become
a successful FBI agent.

24:37.352 --> 24:40.563
You've had
an impressive career.

24:40.563 --> 24:42.982
Anyway,
it got me to thinking

24:42.982 --> 24:44.859
there's an empty
congressional seat

24:44.859 --> 24:48.822
in the 13th District in Michigan
that represents Detroit.

24:48.822 --> 24:52.409
They want somebody
tough on crime.

24:52.409 --> 24:54.536
I think
you would be perfect.

24:54.536 --> 24:56.746
A hometown hero returns.

24:56.746 --> 24:58.915
Me?
A Congressman?

24:58.915 --> 25:00.041
I know.

25:00.041 --> 25:02.877
That's a wild idea, right?

25:02.877 --> 25:07.590
But I'm rarely wrong once
I get a read on someone.

25:07.590 --> 25:10.927
And I could help you
through the process.

25:10.927 --> 25:12.595
First, you'd need
to drop everything

25:12.595 --> 25:13.763
and clear
your schedule.

25:13.763 --> 25:15.598
No, I'm not
dropping anything.

25:17.642 --> 25:19.060
Agent Ressler,
in Congress,

25:19.060 --> 25:21.855
you could reach
so many more people.

25:21.855 --> 25:25.817
You could make
a real difference.

25:25.817 --> 25:28.194
You know, Ms. Foster,
you are worth every penny

25:28.194 --> 25:30.280
those corporate schmucks
pay you.

25:30.280 --> 25:31.573
I'll give you that.

25:31.573 --> 25:33.908
Now,
if you'll excuse me,

25:33.908 --> 25:35.577
I got to get back
to my office.

25:35.577 --> 25:40.832
♪

25:40.832 --> 25:42.792
Thank you
for calling me, Manny.

25:42.792 --> 25:44.753
There he is-- Red.

25:44.753 --> 25:48.923
I just had
the most absolutely

25:48.923 --> 25:51.384
mouthwatering boliche.

25:51.384 --> 25:52.761
Boliche is a bit heavy

25:52.761 --> 25:54.095
for the middle
of the day, no?

25:54.095 --> 25:56.848
I'm finding I prefer
my dinner at lunch,

25:56.848 --> 25:59.100
a light supper
in the evening,

25:59.100 --> 26:00.977
drinks at both.

26:04.230 --> 26:07.233
I assume you've had
a change of mind, yes?

26:07.233 --> 26:08.943
[ Sighs ]

26:08.943 --> 26:10.695
I want to see
the gloves again.

26:10.695 --> 26:13.531
[ Chuckles ]
Alright.

26:13.531 --> 26:18.453
♪

26:18.453 --> 26:21.206
There they are.

26:21.206 --> 26:22.999
The name.

26:26.127 --> 26:28.421
Julian Flores.
And you were right.

26:28.421 --> 26:29.964
He was Special Forces.

26:29.964 --> 26:32.842
He's in Falls Church, Virginia,
living under an alias.

26:32.842 --> 26:35.136
I'll text you the address.

26:35.136 --> 26:37.639
You're not gonna hurt him,
are you?

26:37.639 --> 26:38.890
Why?

26:38.890 --> 26:41.184
I kind of know his uncle.

26:41.184 --> 26:42.977
I like the guy.

26:42.977 --> 26:44.813
He'll be just fine.

26:44.813 --> 26:48.316
♪

26:48.316 --> 26:49.526
[ Sighs ]

26:49.526 --> 26:51.945
[ Sniffs ]

26:51.945 --> 26:55.657
You know, I was gonna give
those to you either way.

26:55.657 --> 26:56.866
What can I say?

26:56.866 --> 26:59.536
I'm a sucker
for a sentimental story.

26:59.536 --> 27:01.413
I appreciate that, Red.

27:03.873 --> 27:05.875
Manny, did you happen
to talk to Weecha

27:05.875 --> 27:08.545
since I saw you yesterday?

27:08.545 --> 27:09.796
I did not.

27:09.796 --> 27:11.464
Well, next time you do,
would you mind

27:11.464 --> 27:12.507
giving her a message?

27:12.507 --> 27:15.552
Do you have a pen?

27:15.552 --> 27:17.345
Here you go.

27:17.345 --> 27:24.978
♪

27:24.978 --> 27:26.688
Cooper: Agent Ressler,
is everything okay?

27:26.688 --> 27:28.231
You were gone a lot longer
than usual.

27:28.231 --> 27:30.734
That's because I was
with Blair Foster.

27:30.734 --> 27:33.153
She ambushed my NA meeting.
Wait, what?

27:33.153 --> 27:34.696
Did she say
Anything incriminating?

27:34.696 --> 27:36.197
Uh, no.

27:36.197 --> 27:38.616
No, she steps right up to
the line without crossing it.

27:38.616 --> 27:39.659
She's bold.

27:39.659 --> 27:41.036
She's not afraid of anyone.

27:41.036 --> 27:43.872
Well, while you were out
with our blacklister,

27:43.872 --> 27:45.415
we think we may have I.D.'d
the researcher

27:45.415 --> 27:49.377
who wrote the report--
Dr. Samuel Feinberg.

27:49.377 --> 27:52.213
He's a researcher at Redlands
Chemical Institute.

27:52.213 --> 27:54.883
And according to their
head of research,

27:54.883 --> 27:58.553
Feinberg conducted several
studies for Moder & Sons

27:58.553 --> 28:00.096
over a 7-year period.

28:00.096 --> 28:04.726
But his relationship with them
ended abruptly in 2017,

28:04.726 --> 28:06.978
which is the same year
the report

28:06.978 --> 28:08.772
Whitaker found
was supposedly written.

28:08.772 --> 28:10.523
So what, they stopped working
with him

28:10.523 --> 28:13.735
because he concluded that their
all-star product causes cancer?

28:13.735 --> 28:15.320
That's what we're thinking.

28:15.320 --> 28:17.030
It's not a sure bet, but it's
the best lead we've got.

28:17.030 --> 28:20.367
Malik, Ressler--
go talk to Dr. Feinberg.

28:20.367 --> 28:22.077
Not only is he our last chance
to get some proof,

28:22.077 --> 28:24.579
but he may be in danger
if Moder & Sons

28:24.579 --> 28:26.081
see him as a threat.

28:26.081 --> 28:27.874
And we could use a win
because I'm just getting word

28:27.874 --> 28:30.377
Judge Hurban
has made her decision.

28:30.377 --> 28:33.463
[ Knock on door ]

28:33.463 --> 28:36.675
Excuse me. Are you
Dr. Samuel Feinberg?

28:36.675 --> 28:37.842
Yes.

28:37.842 --> 28:39.803
Agents Ressler and Malik, FBI.

28:39.803 --> 28:41.221
May we come in?

28:41.221 --> 28:44.432
Of course.
I was expecting you.

28:44.432 --> 28:52.273
♪

28:52.273 --> 28:56.111
This is my attorney,
Blair Foster.

28:56.111 --> 28:59.698
I'd like her to be present
for our conversation.

28:59.698 --> 29:02.409
Agent Ressler,
long time no see.

29:06.079 --> 29:10.375
Mr. Feinberg,
as you may already know,

29:10.375 --> 29:12.627
we're conducting
an investigation

29:12.627 --> 29:14.212
into Moder & Sons.

29:14.212 --> 29:16.673
We understand you did some
research for them at Redlands.

29:16.673 --> 29:18.299
It feels like ages ago now.

29:18.299 --> 29:19.718
But, yes.

29:19.718 --> 29:23.013
To be more specific, we're
interested in a 2017 study

29:23.013 --> 29:24.639
where you concluded that

29:24.639 --> 29:26.725
there was carcinogenic material
in some of their products.

29:26.725 --> 29:28.268
That's not correct.

29:28.268 --> 29:31.146
Are you saying that you
didn't do a study in 2017

29:31.146 --> 29:32.355
on Spring 'N Shine?

29:32.355 --> 29:35.608
I did do a study,
but I never finished it.

29:35.608 --> 29:37.152
The data was unsound.

29:37.152 --> 29:39.320
We have a witness who's willing
to go on record

29:39.320 --> 29:42.323
saying he saw a report
of the study,

29:42.323 --> 29:44.868
a complete
and very damning one

29:44.868 --> 29:46.286
for Moder & Sons.

29:46.286 --> 29:48.163
Ressler: And if this report
comes to light,

29:48.163 --> 29:49.414
and it comes out
that you lied

29:49.414 --> 29:50.874
during a federal investigation,

29:50.874 --> 29:54.502
well, that could end
very poorly for you.

29:54.502 --> 29:57.380
You understand?

29:57.380 --> 30:00.091
If you have any more questions,

30:00.091 --> 30:03.303
you can direct them
to Ms. Foster's office.

30:03.303 --> 30:05.597
I don't have anything
more to say.

30:05.597 --> 30:10.560
♪

30:10.560 --> 30:14.105
He lied right to our faces
like it was nothing.

30:14.105 --> 30:15.857
She promised him something.

30:15.857 --> 30:17.025
Apparently, it was worth
the threat

30:17.025 --> 30:18.902
of a federal
prison sentence.

30:18.902 --> 30:22.072
[ Cellphone rings ]

30:23.698 --> 30:25.450
Red: <i>I tried to get
ahold of Harold,</i>

30:25.450 --> 30:28.203
<i>but I had to settle
for the second string.</i>

30:28.203 --> 30:29.996
I really hope there's a point
to this phone call

30:29.996 --> 30:31.539
other than to insult me.

30:31.539 --> 30:34.584
Donald, I can't think of a
better point than to insult you,

30:34.584 --> 30:36.544
<i>but I suppose this will have
to do for the moment.</i>

30:36.544 --> 30:39.631
<i>I'm calling because I have a
gift for you at the warehouse.</i>

30:39.631 --> 30:44.094
Ms. Foster's operative,
Mr. Julian Flores of Havana.

30:44.094 --> 30:46.888
He's waiting
and he's ready to talk.

30:46.888 --> 30:48.223
How'd you manage that?

30:48.223 --> 30:50.475
Cost me seven favors
at Immigration Services.

30:50.475 --> 30:54.062
It's not so simple to get stamps
on asylum papers these days.

30:54.062 --> 30:55.563
Seven favors?

30:55.563 --> 30:57.065
What'd you do, move his whole
family over from Cuba?

30:57.065 --> 30:59.567
<i>No. His mistress,
her sister,</i>

30:59.567 --> 31:03.279
his mother, two cousins,
a dear friend from high school,

31:03.279 --> 31:05.699
and a dog,
which was its own headache.

31:05.699 --> 31:09.285
I shouldn't have even asked.
Look, we're on our way over now.

31:11.287 --> 31:13.081
Look, I don't want
to belabor this.

31:13.081 --> 31:14.582
You've all heard my thoughts.

31:14.582 --> 31:18.211
And while there were compelling
arguments on both sides,

31:18.211 --> 31:20.922
I'm ruling in favor
of your task force,

31:20.922 --> 31:22.507
Assistant Director Cooper.

31:22.507 --> 31:26.261
It's clear to me that the safety
and security reasons for keeping

31:26.261 --> 31:29.597
your records internal
far outweigh any benefit

31:29.597 --> 31:32.976
Congress might receive
from making them public.

31:32.976 --> 31:34.310
Thank you, Your Honor.

31:34.310 --> 31:38.064
So if you will excuse me,
I am due in court.

31:38.064 --> 31:39.899
I trust you'll see
yourselves out.

31:39.899 --> 31:41.609
[ Door opens ]

31:41.609 --> 31:44.279
[ Sighs ]

31:44.279 --> 31:45.989
Well, there you have it, Clayton.

31:45.989 --> 31:47.449
Can we finally
put this to rest?

31:47.449 --> 31:49.993
Mnh-mnh.
Not today, Cynthia,

31:49.993 --> 31:51.786
because now my interest
is piqued.

31:51.786 --> 31:54.622
Yeah, I thought Hudson
had found political gold

31:54.622 --> 31:56.041
with this investigation.

31:56.041 --> 32:00.128
But based on how badly you want
to keep this secret,

32:00.128 --> 32:02.130
I think he might have
found a diamond mine.

32:02.130 --> 32:06.009
[ Laughing ]
Now you just sound paranoid.

32:06.009 --> 32:07.302
Well, as a courtesy,

32:07.302 --> 32:09.095
I'm gonna give you
a heads up.

32:09.095 --> 32:12.140
I'm holding a press conference
later today.

32:12.140 --> 32:14.184
I'm launching
a formal investigation

32:14.184 --> 32:15.643
into the task force.

32:15.643 --> 32:17.979
And I-- I will be
naming names, Cynthia,

32:17.979 --> 32:20.482
including yours.

32:20.482 --> 32:23.693
I'm more convinced than ever
there's something here.

32:26.863 --> 32:30.492
And we will
get answers.

32:30.492 --> 32:36.414
♪

32:44.714 --> 32:45.507
Are these
really necessary?

32:47.050 --> 32:49.469
Siya: We just wanted you to get
used to the feel of them.

32:49.469 --> 32:52.180
You're gonna be
wearing them a lot real soon.

32:52.180 --> 32:55.767
What could you
possibly have on me?

32:55.767 --> 32:57.435
Flores talked, Blair.

32:57.435 --> 32:59.896
We have him on trespassing, stalking,

32:59.896 --> 33:02.816
larceny,
identity theft.

33:02.816 --> 33:04.734
Well, he was happy
to cut a deal.

33:04.734 --> 33:06.152
Sang like a robin.

33:06.152 --> 33:08.113
I'm supposed to be afraid?

33:08.113 --> 33:10.115
No, you should be aware.

33:10.115 --> 33:13.076
He's implicated you on
multiple federal counts.

33:13.076 --> 33:16.121
You're looking
at 10 years.

33:16.121 --> 33:19.207
I have been in badly lit rooms
like this one

33:19.207 --> 33:21.251
more times
than I can count.

33:21.251 --> 33:22.877
It's always the same song
and dance.

33:22.877 --> 33:24.587
So let's cut
to the deal making,

33:24.587 --> 33:26.881
because I'm certainly
not going to prison.

33:26.881 --> 33:29.592
That's awfully arrogant
of you.

33:29.592 --> 33:30.969
It's awfully naive of you

33:30.969 --> 33:34.097
to think it would go
any other way.

33:34.097 --> 33:36.850
Alright, let's say hypothetically,

33:36.850 --> 33:38.393
we were willing to play ball.

33:38.393 --> 33:40.687
Flores said that you keep
meticulous records

33:40.687 --> 33:41.938
on all your clients--

33:41.938 --> 33:44.107
records that only
you have access to.

33:44.107 --> 33:45.859
Now, you hand over those files
to us,

33:45.859 --> 33:47.527
including the one
on Moder & Sons,

33:47.527 --> 33:52.532
and we might be able to work out
a generous immunity agreement.

33:52.532 --> 33:55.118
All of my files?
[ Laughs ]

33:55.118 --> 33:57.537
That's not gonna happen, Don.

33:57.537 --> 33:59.122
There's things in some
of those files

33:59.122 --> 34:01.332
that would get me
killed twice over.

34:01.332 --> 34:04.544
That was some fancy pitching,
but ball season's over.

34:04.544 --> 34:06.880
I'll risk my day
in court.

34:06.880 --> 34:09.716
No files, no deal.

34:09.716 --> 34:13.428
Look, the fact that the FBI
even got this far

34:13.428 --> 34:16.931
tells me there's someone bigger
behind all of this.

34:16.931 --> 34:18.558
So who's really
in charge here?

34:18.558 --> 34:21.144
And what is it
they want from me?

34:21.144 --> 34:23.563
I'm sure we can find
common ground.

34:23.563 --> 34:25.273
There's plenty
I'm willing to share,

34:25.273 --> 34:28.276
but I only deal
in specifics.

34:28.276 --> 34:30.862
[ Cellphone rings ]

34:30.862 --> 34:32.155
Harold,
what can I do for you?

34:32.155 --> 34:34.407
I assume you received my gift.

34:34.407 --> 34:37.452
We did, and he's the gift
that keeps on giving.

34:37.452 --> 34:39.162
We were able
to bring in Foster

34:39.162 --> 34:40.455
based on Flores'
testimony,

34:40.455 --> 34:42.290
and she's willing
to make a deal.

34:42.290 --> 34:45.335
But she'll only give us
precise information.

34:45.335 --> 34:50.006
Yes. Well, I suspected she'd be
a formidable opponent.

34:50.006 --> 34:52.592
I want to do
the maximum good here.

34:52.592 --> 34:54.219
Dorf is about to have
a press conference,

34:54.219 --> 34:55.679
and he's naming names

34:55.679 --> 34:57.847
<i>in the hope that enough
political pressure</i>

34:57.847 --> 35:00.600
<i>will eventually force us
to show our hands.</i>

35:00.600 --> 35:02.811
We could be done here.

35:02.811 --> 35:04.187
This could be
our last case.

35:04.187 --> 35:06.022
<i>I wouldn't be so sure
about that.</i>

35:06.022 --> 35:08.483
If Ms. Foster wants
to be specific,

35:08.483 --> 35:13.029
ask her about
December 31, 2013.

35:13.029 --> 35:14.989
See what she has to say.

35:14.989 --> 35:16.241
That's all?
Just that date.

35:16.241 --> 35:18.493
<i>Oh, it'll be enough.</i>

35:18.493 --> 35:23.289
♪

35:23.289 --> 35:25.208
If you want to cut a deal,
you'll need to turn over

35:25.208 --> 35:27.210
everything
on Moder & Sons...

35:27.210 --> 35:31.965
and any information
regarding December 31, 2013.

35:31.965 --> 35:33.591
There it is.

35:33.591 --> 35:36.219
Now we're all playing
on the same field.

35:36.219 --> 35:38.513
Care to elaborate
on that?

35:38.513 --> 35:41.224
I'll tell you every
sordid detail...

35:41.224 --> 35:44.436
as soon as I have
my deal in writing.

35:44.436 --> 35:47.230
"And I would like
to tell you,

35:47.230 --> 35:50.066
as many of you may
know, the..."

35:50.066 --> 35:52.569
It's too late, Harold.
No, I'm on in 15.

35:52.569 --> 35:54.404
Nothing you can say
will deter me.

35:54.404 --> 35:56.031
I'm holding this
press conference.

35:56.031 --> 35:59.242
I understand, but I'm actually
here on other business.

35:59.242 --> 36:01.202
You see,
Blair Foster sent me.

36:01.202 --> 36:10.378
♪

36:10.378 --> 36:12.088
Thank you all
for coming out today.

36:12.088 --> 36:14.841
I apologize for the delay.

36:14.841 --> 36:16.634
I'll keep it brief.

36:19.429 --> 36:21.598
It's with a heavy heart
that I must report

36:21.598 --> 36:26.102
that due
to personal family matters,

36:26.102 --> 36:28.063
I will be taking
a leave of absence

36:28.063 --> 36:30.774
from my position
effective immediately.

36:30.774 --> 36:32.317
Reporter: Senator!

36:32.317 --> 36:36.279
It's been my honor
to serve this country.

36:36.279 --> 36:39.115
I would appreciate privacy
at this time.

36:39.115 --> 36:40.950
Thank you.
Senator Dorf!

36:40.950 --> 36:42.577
[ Reporters yelling questions ]

36:42.577 --> 36:46.706
♪

36:46.706 --> 36:50.210
I'm sorry. The senator won't be
taking any questions.

36:58.802 --> 36:59.511
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

37:00.178 --> 37:04.015
[ Speaks Spanish ]

37:05.934 --> 37:08.561
Weecha.

37:08.561 --> 37:10.897
Come in. Come in.
Sit down.

37:10.897 --> 37:18.488
♪

37:18.488 --> 37:20.115
He was in again.

37:20.115 --> 37:22.325
Asking about you.

37:22.325 --> 37:24.744
Did you tell him
that we had been speaking?

37:24.744 --> 37:27.163
No.

37:27.163 --> 37:30.417
Oh, he is persistent,
isn't he?

37:30.417 --> 37:33.003
He told me to tell you
something if I saw you.

37:33.003 --> 37:34.546
He wrote it down.

37:34.546 --> 37:47.559
♪

37:47.559 --> 37:50.020
I don't know what I'm going
to do with that man.

37:50.020 --> 37:52.647
<i>En serio.</i>

37:54.065 --> 37:55.400
You and me both.

37:55.400 --> 37:59.029
♪

37:59.029 --> 38:01.239
[ Knock on door ]

38:03.116 --> 38:04.951
Sure is quiet
around here.

38:04.951 --> 38:06.619
The rest of the team
is out arresting

38:06.619 --> 38:09.205
the C.E.O.
of Moder & Sons.

38:09.205 --> 38:11.624
Well, that's sure
to make the 11:00 news.

38:11.624 --> 38:15.837
Speaking of, Senator Dorf
did a real 180.

38:15.837 --> 38:17.756
It's everywhere.

38:17.756 --> 38:19.591
That had to be your work.

38:19.591 --> 38:22.802
How'd you get him
to change his mind?

38:22.802 --> 38:26.014
Blackmail.

38:26.014 --> 38:28.850
Good Lord, Harold.

38:28.850 --> 38:30.143
Do I even want to know?

38:30.143 --> 38:32.062
Foster had a file on him.

38:32.062 --> 38:34.397
New Year's Eve, 2013.

38:34.397 --> 38:35.815
Dorf's teenage son Michael

38:35.815 --> 38:38.651
was driving high
and drunk after a party.

38:38.651 --> 38:40.070
He miscalculated a turn

38:40.070 --> 38:42.030
and hit a teenage girl,
Makayla Johnson.

38:42.030 --> 38:43.990
She was waiting
on a city bus.

38:43.990 --> 38:45.200
He paralyzed her
from the waist down.

38:45.200 --> 38:47.827
Whoo. Wow.
That's awful.

38:47.827 --> 38:49.079
It's terrible.

38:49.079 --> 38:50.497
When his son was taken
to the hospital,

38:50.497 --> 38:53.541
Dorf used Foster to ensure
the blood was never tested,

38:53.541 --> 38:55.710
so it all went away
without criminal charges.

38:55.710 --> 38:58.046
Wasn't his entire
political platform

38:58.046 --> 38:59.673
based on
being tough on drugs?

38:59.673 --> 39:02.759
Yes. So he was hell bent
on burying it.

39:02.759 --> 39:04.678
Apparently, his son was
incredibly remorseful.

39:04.678 --> 39:06.554
He wanted to pay
for what he'd done.

39:06.554 --> 39:10.767
So Dorf used Foster
to silence his own son.

39:10.767 --> 39:13.311
Michael Dorf has been in
and out of psychological care

39:13.311 --> 39:14.854
since the accident.

39:14.854 --> 39:17.899
Trust me, if anyone
understands the need

39:17.899 --> 39:19.359
to bury certain things

39:19.359 --> 39:20.944
when it comes to family,
it's me.

39:20.944 --> 39:24.114
But are we really
just gonna let Dorf off

39:24.114 --> 39:26.783
for obstructing justice?
Not exactly.

39:26.783 --> 39:27.951
[ Knock on door ]

39:27.951 --> 39:29.911
Senator Dorf and I
came to an arrangement.

39:29.911 --> 39:34.582
♪

39:34.582 --> 39:35.959
It's late.
I'm just leaving.

39:35.959 --> 39:37.836
Who got to you?
What the hell happened?

39:37.836 --> 39:40.255
Blair Foster happened.
Oh, the lawyer?

39:40.255 --> 39:41.631
What does she have to do
with any of this?

39:41.631 --> 39:43.133
It doesn't matter.
She doesn't matter.

39:43.133 --> 39:45.343
What matters is this
is all over.

39:45.343 --> 39:46.803
It's time to move on.

39:46.803 --> 39:48.638
Are you kidding me?
This-- whatever this is--

39:48.638 --> 39:50.598
it just continues to prove
my theory

39:50.598 --> 39:52.183
that something bigger
is going on out here...

39:52.183 --> 39:53.810
Well, I'm moving on, alright?

39:53.810 --> 39:56.354
I'm done with this.
I'm done with us.

39:56.354 --> 39:57.772
And I'm sure
you won't listen,

39:57.772 --> 40:01.359
but if I may offer some
parting advice, here goes--

40:01.359 --> 40:04.112
Leave this alone.

40:04.112 --> 40:05.363
You're smart.

40:05.363 --> 40:07.365
You have your whole career
ahead of you.

40:07.365 --> 40:09.325
No good will come of this.

40:09.325 --> 40:12.162
I'm certain of that.

40:12.162 --> 40:14.372
Go home, Mr. Hudson.

40:15.874 --> 40:19.002
So Makayla Johnson's therapy
and medical expenses

40:19.002 --> 40:20.503
will be paid for
by the Dorfs?

40:20.503 --> 40:22.839
For the rest of her life
and more.

40:22.839 --> 40:27.010
I guess that's a form
of restorative justice.

40:27.010 --> 40:28.345
That was my hope.

40:28.345 --> 40:31.389
And the task force
lives to see another day.

40:31.389 --> 40:33.892
What about Foster?

40:33.892 --> 40:35.185
She's a free woman.

40:35.185 --> 40:38.355
We had to let her go
to get what we needed.

40:38.355 --> 40:41.649
I'm not convinced Hudson
will ever give this up.

40:41.649 --> 40:44.319
What can we say?
He's on a crusade.

40:44.319 --> 40:46.988
It's a dog with a bone.

40:46.988 --> 40:50.200
I kind of...
admire the guy.

40:50.200 --> 40:52.702
Strangely, so do I.

40:52.702 --> 40:54.913
That said, with Dorf
out of the way,

40:54.913 --> 40:57.457
I'm not sure there's anyone
who can help the defeated

40:57.457 --> 41:00.210
Mr. Hudson continue
his offensive.

41:00.210 --> 41:02.295
[ Cellphone ringing ]

41:02.295 --> 41:09.636
♪

41:09.636 --> 41:11.012
Hello?

41:11.012 --> 41:12.347
Congressman Hudson.

41:12.347 --> 41:14.391
It's Blair Foster.

41:14.391 --> 41:16.434
<i>I realize you're relatively
new in town,</i>

41:16.434 --> 41:19.270
<i>but I'm sure you've heard
my name by now.</i>

41:19.270 --> 41:22.023
I'd like to set a meeting
with you.

41:22.023 --> 41:23.191
Regarding what?

41:23.191 --> 41:24.567
How did you even get
this number?

41:24.567 --> 41:25.819
<i>I know today's little
press conference</i>

41:25.819 --> 41:27.529
<i>didn't go the way
you'd hoped,</i>

41:27.529 --> 41:30.865
and that you were counting
on the support of Senator Dorf.

41:30.865 --> 41:33.618
I have some information
I'd like to share with you.

41:33.618 --> 41:35.161
I think
it could be the start

41:35.161 --> 41:38.123
of a mutually
beneficial relationship.

41:38.123 --> 41:39.582
I'm not sure.

41:39.582 --> 41:42.836
I don't think we really play
the game the same way.

41:42.836 --> 41:44.212
I get that.

41:44.212 --> 41:45.588
I do.

41:45.588 --> 41:47.549
In my experience,
though--

41:47.549 --> 41:50.593
it never hurts
to take the meeting.

41:50.593 --> 41:53.680
So...
what's it gonna be?

42:00.311 --> 42:32.719
♪
